{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891871425,"sessionID":"ses_2849bfcc3ffeMnzI8RQVHE0I1w","part":{"id":"prt_d7b64fca0001yLneulDRmWjHwN","messageID":"msg_d7b64d43f001VJ3ZSqbmKa3ok4","sessionID":"ses_2849bfcc3ffeMnzI8RQVHE0I1w","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: CLI Invoke and Status Commands (AR-023)\n\n## AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status 命令\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `cmd/cli` |\n| **Language** | Python |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the `invoke` and `status` commands for the AgentCube CLI to complete the agent lifecycle management workflow: `pack` → `build` → `publish` → `invoke` → `status`.\n\nThe `invoke` command SHALL:\n- Send JSON payloads to deployed agents via HTTP POST requests\n- Support custom HTTP headers for authentication and metadata\n- Handle both AgentRuntime CR and standard Kubernetes deployments\n- Automatically manage session IDs for AgentRuntime invocations\n- Parse and display agent responses with proper formatting\n\nThe `status` command SHALL:\n- Retrieve and display the current deployment status of agents\n- Support both AgentRuntime CR and standard Kubernetes providers\n- Present status information in a Rich Table format\n- Exit with code 1 when agent is not published or in error state\n- Provide clear guidance for next steps based on status\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n1. **CLI Command Implementation - `invoke`**\n   - Add `invoke` subcommand to the Typer CLI application\n   - Command options:\n     - `workspace` (`-f`, `--workspace`): Path to agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n     - `payload` (`--payload`): JSON-formatted input passed to the agent (default: \"{}\")\n     - `header_list` (`--header`): Custom HTTP headers, repeatable (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token')\n     - `provider` (`--provider`): Target provider - 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service) [default: \"agentcube\"]\n     - `verbose` (`--verbose`): Enable detailed logging\n\n2. **CLI Command Implementation - `status`**\n   - Add `status` subcommand to the Typer CLI application\n   - Command options:\n     - `workspace` (`-f`, `--workspace`): Path to agent workspace directory (default: \".\")\n     - `provider` (`--provider`): Target provider - 'agentcube' or 'k8s' [default: \"agentcube\"]\n     - `verbose` (`--verbose`): Enable detailed logging\n\n3. **InvokeRuntime Implementation**\n   - `InvokeRuntime` class in `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n   - Core methods:\n     - `invoke(workspace_path, payload, headers)`: Main invocation orchestration\n     - `_validate_invoke_prerequisites()`: Validate workspace and metadata\n     - `_invoke_agent_via_agentcube()`: Invoke via AgentRuntime CR\n     - `_direct_http_invocation()`: Direct HTTP invocation for K8s deployments\n     - URL rewriting for AgentRuntime CR invocations\n\n4. **StatusRuntime Implementation**\n   - `StatusRuntime` class in `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n   - Core methods:\n     - `get_status(workspace_path, provider)`: Main status retrieval\n     - `_get_k8s_status()`: Get status from Kubernetes Deployment\n     - `_get_cr_k8s_status()`: Get status from AgentRuntime CR\n   - Status value mapping and presentation\n\n5. **HTTP Client Integration**\n   - Async HTTP client for AgentRuntime invocations\n   - Synchronous HTTP client for K8s deployments\n   - Session header management (`X-Agentcube-Session-Id`)\n   - Payload validation and JSON parsing\n   - Header format validation (`key:value`)\n\n6. **Error Handling**\n   - Invalid JSON payload detection and reporting\n   - Invalid header format validation\n   - Missing agent_id / not_published state handling\n   - HTTP error responses with status codes\n   - Timeout handling for invocations\n   - Integration with `_handle_error()` for consistent CLI patterns\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n1. **Agent Development**: Agent business logic implementation\n2. **Persistent Sessions**: Session management beyond single invocation\n3. **Streaming Responses**: Chunked/streaming HTTP response handling\n4. **Load Testing**: Concurrent invocation or performance testing features\n5. **Log Streaming**: Real-time log tailing from agents\n6. **Multi-Agent Orchestration**: Invoking multiple agents in sequence/parallel\n7. **GraphQL Support**: Alternative query language support\n8. **WebSocket Communication**: Persistent connection protocols\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### Invoke Command Flow\n\n```\ninvoke(workspace, payload, headers, provider)\n    │\n    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Parse Payload               │\n│ - Validate JSON format      │\n│ - Exit code 1 if invalid    │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Parse Headers               │\n│ - Validate key:value format │\n│ - Exit code 1 if invalid    │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Load Metadata               │\n│ - Read agent_metadata.yaml  │\n│ - Check agent_id exists     │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Validate Prerequisites      │\n│ - Workspace exists          │\n│ - agent_endpoint present    │\n│ - k8s_deployment info       │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ├─ agentcube ─────► Build AgentRuntime URL\n              │                   - {router}/v1/namespaces/{ns}/\n              │                     agent-runtimes/{name}/invocations/\n              │                   - Add session header\n              │\n              └─ k8s ───────────► Use agent_endpoint directly\n                                  - Direct HTTP POST\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Execute HTTP Request        │\n│ - POST with payload         │\n│ - Include custom headers    │\n│ - Add session header (CR)   │\n│ - Handle timeouts           │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Process Response            │\n│ - Parse JSON response       │\n│ - Display formatted result  │\n│ - Update metadata (CR)      │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n         Return Result\n```\n\n### Status Command Flow\n\n```\nstatus(workspace, provider)\n    │\n    ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Load Metadata               │\n│ - Read agent_metadata.yaml  │\n│ - Check agent_id exists     │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Check Published State       │\n│ - If no agent_id:           │\n│   → \"not_published\"         │\n│   → Exit code 1             │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ├─ agentcube ─────► Query AgentRuntime CR\n              │                   - get_agent_runtime()\n              │                   - Extract status field\n              │                   - Check agentEndpoint\n              │\n              └─ k8s ───────────► Query K8s Deployment/Service\n                                  - get_agent_status()\n                                  - Check ready replicas\n                                  - Get service info\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Build Status Table          │\n│ - Rich Table formatting     │\n│ - Color-coded status        │\n│ - Deployment details        │\n└─────────────┬───────────────┘\n              │\n              ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────┐\n│ Handle Status Result        │\n│ - \"ready\": success (exit 0) │\n│ - \"error\": exit 1           │\n│ - \"not_found\": exit 1       │\n│ - \"not_published\": exit 1   │\n└─────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### InvokeRuntime Class Structure\n\n```python\nclass InvokeRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n    \"\"\"Initialize with provider selection.\"\"\"\n\n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n    ) -> Any: ...\n    \"\"\"Main entry point for agent invocation.\"\"\"\n\n    def _validate_invoke_prerequisites(\n        self, workspace_path: Path\n    ) -> Tuple[AgentMetadata, str, str]: ...\n    \"\"\"Validate workspace and extract endpoint info.\"\"\"\n\n    async def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n        self,\n        agent_id: str,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n        endpoint: str,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n    ) -> Any: ...\n    \"\"\"Invoke via AgentRuntime CR with session management.\"\"\"\n\n    async def _direct_http_invocation(\n        self,\n        endpoint: str,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n        workspace_path: Path,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Direct HTTP invocation for K8s deployments.\"\"\"\n```\n\n### StatusRuntime Class Structure\n\n```python\nclass StatusRuntime:\n    def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False, provider: str = \"agentcube\") -> None: ...\n    \"\"\"Initialize with provider selection.\"\"\"\n\n    def get_status(\n        self,\n        workspace_path: Path,\n        provider: Optional[str] = None,\n    ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Main entry point for status retrieval.\"\"\"\n\n    def _get_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Get status from standard Kubernetes Deployment.\"\"\"\n\n    def _get_cr_k8s_status(self, metadata: AgentMetadata) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n    \"\"\"Get status from AgentRuntime CR.\"\"\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Interface\n\n### Typer Invoke Command Signature\n\n```python\ndef invoke(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\n        \".\",\n        \"-f\",\n        \"--workspace\",\n        help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\",\n        show_default=True,\n    ),\n    payload: str = typer.Option(\n        \"{}\",\n        \"--payload\",\n        help=\"JSON-formatted input passed to the agent\",\n    ),\n    header_list: Optional[List[str]] = typer.Option(\n        None,\n        \"--header\",\n        help=\"Custom HTTP headers (e.g., 'Authorization: Bearer token'). Can be specified multiple times.\",\n    ),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\n        \"agentcube\",\n        \"--provider\",\n        help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\",\n    ),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(\n        False,\n        \"--verbose\",\n        help=\"Enable detailed logging\",\n    ),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n### Typer Status Command Signature\n\n```python\ndef status(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\n        \".\",\n        \"-f\",\n        \"--workspace\",\n        help=\"Path to the agent workspace directory\",\n        show_default=True,\n    ),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\n        \"agentcube\",\n        \"--provider\",\n        help=\"Target provider: 'agentcube' (AgentRuntime CR) or 'k8s' (Deployment/Service)\",\n    ),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(\n        False,\n        \"--verbose\",\n        help=\"Enable detailed logging\",\n    ),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n### Command Options Reference\n\n**Invoke Command:**\n\n| Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workspace` | `-f` | str | \".\" | Path to agent workspace directory |\n| `--payload` | | str | \"{}\" | JSON-formatted input passed to agent |\n| `--header` | | List[str] | None | Custom HTTP headers (repeatable) |\n| `--provider` | | str | \"agentcube\" | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' |\n| `--verbose` | | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n\n**Status Command:**\n\n| Option | Short | Type | Default | Description |\n|--------|-------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workspace` | `-f` | str | \".\" | Path to agent workspace directory |\n| `--provider` | | str | \"agentcube\" | Target provider: 'agentcube' or 'k8s' |\n| `--verbose` | | bool | False | Enable detailed logging |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation\n\n### Payload Parsing and Validation\n\n```python\ndef _parse_payload(payload_str: str) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Parse and validate JSON payload.\n\n    Args:\n        payload_str: JSON string to parse.\n\n    Returns:\n        Parsed JSON dictionary.\n\n    Raises:\n        typer.Exit: If JSON is invalid (exit code 1).\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        return json.loads(payload_str)\n    except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\n        console.print(f\"Invalid JSON payload: {e}\", style=\"red\")\n        raise typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n### Header Parsing and Validation\n\n```python\ndef _parse_headers(header_list: Optional[List[str]]) -> Dict[str, str]:\n    \"\"\"Parse header strings into dictionary.\n\n    Args:\n        header_list: List of header strings in 'key:value' format.\n\n    Returns:\n        Dictionary of headers.\n\n    Raises:\n        typer.Exit: If header format is invalid (exit code 1).\n    \"\"\"\n    headers = {}\n    if header_list:\n        for header in header_list:\n            if \":\" not in header:\n                console.print(\n                    f\"Invalid header format: '{header}'. Expected 'key:value'\",\n                    style=\"red\"\n                )\n                raise typer.Exit(1)\n            key, value = header.split(\":\", 1)\n            headers[key.strip()] = value.strip()\n    return headers\n```\n\n### AgentCube Provider Invocation\n\n```python\nasync def _invoke_agent_via_agentcube(\n    self,\n    agent_id: str,\n    payload: Dict[str, Any],\n    headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n    endpoint: str,\n    workspace_path: Path,\n) -> Any:\n    \"\"\"Invoke via AgentRuntime CR.\n\n    1. Rewrite URL to AgentRuntime invocation endpoint\n    2. Add session header if metadata contains session_id\n    3. POST payload with headers\n    4. Return response\n    \"\"\"\n    import httpx\n\n    metadata = self.metadata_service.load_metadata(workspace_path)\n\n    # Rewrite URL for AgentRuntime CR\n    # From: {router_url}/v1/agents/{agent_name}\n    # To: {router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\n    if metadata.k8s_deployment and metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"type\") == \"AgentRuntime\":\n        namespace = metadata.k8s_deployment.get(\"namespace\", \"default\")\n        base_url = metadata.router_url.rstrip(\"/\")\n        invocation_url = f\"{base_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_id}/invocations/\"\n    else:\n        invocation_url = endpoint\n\n    # Prepare headers\n    request_headers = headers.copy() if headers else {}\n    if metadata.session_id:\n        request_headers[\"X-Agentcube-Session-Id\"] = metadata.session_id\n\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        response = await client.post(\n            invocation_url,\n            json=payload,\n            headers=request_headers,\n            timeout=30.0,\n        )\n        response.raise_for_status()\n        return response.json()\n```\n\n### K8s Provider Invocation\n\n```python\nasync def _direct_http_invocation(\n    self,\n    endpoint: str,\n    payload: Dict[str, Any],\n    headers: Optional[Dict[str, str]],\n    workspace_path: Path,\n) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Direct HTTP invocation for K8s deployments.\"\"\"\n    import httpx\n\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        response = await client.post(\n            endpoint,\n            json=payload,\n            headers=headers or {},\n            timeout=30.0,\n        )\n        response.raise_for_status()\n        return response.json()\n```\n\n### Status Display with Rich Table\n\n```python\ndef _display_status_table(status: Dict[str, Any]) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Display status in a Rich Table format.\n\n    Args:\n        status: Status dictionary from get_status().\n    \"\"\"\n    from rich.table import Table\n\n    table = Table(title=\"Agent Status\")\n    table.add_column(\"Property\", style=\"cyan\")\n    table.add_column(\"Value\", style=\"green\")\n\n    # Map status values to colors\n    status_value = status.get(\"status\", \"unknown\")\n    if status_value == \"ready\":\n        status_display = \"[green]ready[/green]\"\n    elif status_value == \"error\":\n        status_display = \"[red]error[/red]\"\n    elif status_value == \"not_published\":\n        status_display = \"[yellow]not_published[/yellow]\"\n    elif status_value == \"not_found\":\n        status_display = \"[red]not_found[/red]\"\n    else:\n        status_display = f\"[yellow]{status_value}[/yellow]\"\n\n    table.add_row(\"Status\", status_display)\n    table.add_row(\"Agent Name\", status.get(\"agent_name\", \"N/A\"))\n    table.add_row(\"Agent ID\", status.get(\"agent_id\", \"N/A\"))\n    table.add_row(\"Provider\", status.get(\"provider\", \"N/A\"))\n    table.add_row(\"Namespace\", status.get(\"namespace\", \"N/A\"))\n\n    if status.get(\"agent_endpoint\"):\n        table.add_row(\"Endpoint\", status[\"agent_endpoint\"])\n\n    if status.get(\"deployment\"):\n        dep = status[\"deployment\"]\n        table.add_row(\"Replicas\", f\"{dep.get('ready_replicas', 0)}/{dep.get('replicas', 0)}\")\n\n    console.print(table)\n```\n\n### Error Handling Pattern\n\nAll errors SHALL propagate through `_handle_error()`:\n\n| Error | Condition | Handling |\n|-------|-----------|----------|\n| `json.JSONDecodeError` | Invalid payload JSON | Print error, exit code 1 |\n| `ValueError` | Invalid header format | Print format guidance, exit code 1 |\n| `FileNotFoundError` | Missing metadata | \"No metadata file found\", exit code 1 |\n| `ValueError` | Not published (no agent_id) | \"Agent not published. Run 'publish' first\", exit code 1 |\n| `httpx.HTTPStatusError` | HTTP error response | Print status code and body, exit code 1 |\n| `TimeoutError` | Request timeout | \"Invocation timed out\", exit code 1 |\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Affected Components\n\n| Component | Impact Level | Description |\n|-----------|--------------|-------------|\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | High | New `invoke` and `status` command registrations and option handling |\n| `agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py` | High | Full implementation of `InvokeRuntime` class (~200 lines) |\n| `agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py` | High | Full implementation of `StatusRuntime` class (~150 lines) |\n| `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Medium | Export `InvokeRuntime` and `StatusRuntime` classes |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Low | Add `InvokeRuntime` and `StatusRuntime` to exports |\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Low | Metadata read for endpoint and deployment info |\n| `agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py` | Medium | `get_agent_status()` for CR status queries |\n| `agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py` | Medium | `get_agent_status()` for K8s status queries |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n**Required:**\n- `publish` command must be executed before `invoke`/`status` (validated via metadata `agent_id`)\n- `httpx>=0.24.0` for async HTTP client (already in dependencies)\n- `AgentMetadata` model for configuration and endpoint tracking\n- Kubernetes cluster access for status queries\n\n**Dependent:**\n- Future monitoring commands may depend on `status` output format\n- CI/CD pipelines may script around `status` exit codes\n\n### Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Endpoint URL mismatch | Medium | High | Clear URL construction logging in verbose mode |\n| Session ID expiration | Medium | Medium | Document session lifecycle; provide re-auth guidance |\n| Network connectivity issues | Medium | Medium | Timeout handling with clear error messages |\n| JSON parsing edge cases | Low | Medium | Strict JSON validation with clear error messages |\n| Status query permissions | Medium | High | Document RBAC requirements |\n\n### Performance Characteristics\n\n| Operation | Time (est.) | Notes |\n|-----------|-------------|-------|\n| `invoke` (AgentRuntime) | 100ms - 5s | Depends on agent response time |\n| `invoke` (K8s direct) | 50ms - 2s | Direct HTTP, no session overhead |\n| `status` | 500ms - 2s | K8s API query time |\n| JSON parsing | <10ms | Small payload validation |\n| Table rendering | <50ms | Rich UI formatting |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Synchronous-only HTTP Client\n\n**Approach**: Use only `requests` library instead of `httpx` for both sync and async operations.\n\n**Rejected**: `httpx` is already a project dependency and provides better async support for future enhancements. The spec calls out async patterns for AgentRuntime invocations.\n\n### Alternative 2: Automatic Provider Detection\n\n**Approach**: Detect provider automatically from metadata `k8s_deployment.type` without requiring `--provider` flag.\n\n**Partially Accepted**: Provider flag is kept for explicitness, but default is derived from metadata if available. CLI still accepts explicit override.\n\n### Alternative 3: Persistent Session Cache\n\n**Approach**: Cache session IDs to disk for reuse across CLI invocations.\n\n**Deferred**: Adds complexity and security concerns. Sessions are managed per-invocation as per current spec. Can be added later if needed.\n\n### Alternative 4: Structured Output (JSON)\n\n**Approach**: Add `--output=json` flag for machine-readable output.\n\n**Deferred**: Future enhancement. Current implementation focuses on human-readable Rich tables and formatted JSON responses.\n\n### Alternative 5: Interactive Invocation Mode\n\n**Approach**: Support interactive mode for multiple invocations with session reuse.\n\n**Rejected**: Out of scope for this AR. The CLI follows a one-shot command pattern consistent with other lifecycle commands.\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n### Invoke Command Verification\n\n```bash\n# Prerequisites: pack, build, and publish commands executed\nkubectl-agentcube pack -f /tmp/test-agent --agent-name test-agent\nkubectl-agentcube build -f /tmp/test-agent\nkubectl-agentcube publish -f /tmp/test-agent --provider k8s --namespace default\n\n# Basic invocation with empty payload\necho '{\"message\": \"hello\"}' | kubectl-agentcube invoke -f /tmp/test-agent \\\n  --payload '{\"input\": \"test\"}' \\\n  --provider k8s\n\n# Invocation with custom headers\nkubectl-agentcube invoke -f /tmp/test-agent \\\n  --payload '{\"query\": \"status\"}' \\\n  --header \"Authorization: Bearer test-token\" \\\n  --header \"X-Custom-Header: value\" \\\n  --verbose\n\n# Test invalid JSON payload\nkubectl-agentcube invoke -f /tmp/test-agent --payload \"not valid json\" 2>&1 | \\\n  grep -q \"Invalid JSON\" && echo \"JSON validation works\"\n\n# Test invalid header format\nkubectl-agentcube invoke -f /tmp/test-agent --header \"no-colon-here\" 2>&1 | \\\n  grep -q \"key:value\" && echo \"Header validation works\"\n```\n\n### Status Command Verification\n\n```bash\n# Check status of published agent\nkubectl-agentcube status -f /tmp/test-agent --provider k8s\n\n# Should display Rich table with status\n\n# Check status before publish (should exit 1)\nkubectl-agentcube pack -f /tmp/new-agent --agent-name new-agent\nkubectl-agentcube status -f /tmp/new-agent 2>&1 | \\\n  grep -q \"not published\" && echo \"Not published detection works\"\n\n# Verify exit code on not_published\nkubectl-agentcube status -f /tmp/new-agent 2>/dev/null || \\\n  [ $? -eq 1 ] && echo \"Exit code 1 on not_published works\"\n\n# AgentCube provider status\nkubectl-agentcube publish -f /tmp/test-agent --provider agentcube \\\n  --namespace default\nkubectl-agentcube status -f /tmp/test-agent --provider agentcube\n```\n\n### Error Handling Verification\n\n```bash\n# Test missing metadata\nkubectl-agentcube invoke -f /tmp/no-metadata 2>&1 | \\\n  grep -q \"metadata\" && echo \"Missing metadata error works\"\n\n# Test timeout (with slow agent)\nkubectl-agentcube invoke -f /tmp/test-agent \\\n  --payload '{\"sleep\": 60}' \\\n  --verbose 2>&1 | grep -q \"timeout\" && echo \"Timeout handling works\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [cli-toolkit/design.md](cli-toolkit/design.md) — Detailed CLI design specifications\n- [cli-toolkit/spec.md](cli-toolkit/spec.md) — Complete requirements specification\n- [python-sdk/design.md](python-sdk/design.md) — Python SDK for session management patterns\n- [python-sdk/spec.md](python-sdk/spec.md) — SDK HTTP contracts\n- [deployment/client-go.md](deployment/client-go.md) — client-go library for AgentRuntime CR\n- AR-020 — CLI Pack Command\n- AR-021 — CLI Build Command\n- AR-022 — CLI Publish Command — Predecessor in lifecycle\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n### Invoke Command\n\n1. ✅ `invoke` command is registered in Typer CLI with all specified options\n2. ✅ `InvokeRuntime` class implements all required methods per spec\n3. ✅ JSON payload parsing validates input and exits code 1 on invalid JSON\n4. ✅ Header parsing validates `key:value` format and exits code 1 on invalid\n5. ✅ AgentCube provider (`agentcube`) invocations use AgentRuntime URL format\n6. ✅ Session header (`X-Agentcube-Session-Id`) added when metadata contains `session_id`\n7. ✅ K8s provider (`k8s`) uses direct HTTP POST to `agent_endpoint`\n8. ✅ Response is parsed as JSON and displayed formatted\n9. ✅ HTTP errors are caught and displayed with status code\n10. ✅ Missing `agent_id` produces clear \"not published\" error with exit code 1\n11. ✅ All errors use consistent `_handle_error()` pattern\n12. ✅ Verbose mode enables DEBUG logging and full tracebacks\n\n### Status Command\n\n1. ✅ `status` command is registered in Typer CLI with all specified options\n2. ✅ `StatusRuntime` class implements all required methods per spec\n3. ✅ AgentCube provider queries AgentRuntime CR status\n4. ✅ K8s provider queries standard K8s Deployment status\n5. ✅ Status displayed in Rich Table format with color coding\n6. ✅ `not_published` status (no `agent_id`) exits with code 1\n7. ✅ `error` or `not_found` status exits with code 1\n8. ✅ `ready` status exits with code 0\n9. ✅ Table includes: status, agent_name, agent_id, provider, namespace, endpoint, replicas\n10. ✅ All errors use consistent `_handle_error()` pattern\n11. ✅ Verbose mode enables DEBUG logging\n\n---\n\n*AR-023 — Module: cmd/cli — Language: Python — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/services/agentcube_provider.py\">\nERROR [209:9] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"value\" of type \"str\" in function \"__setitem__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\nERROR [210:9] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"value\" of type \"str\" in function \"__setitem__\"\n  Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\n    \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/agentcube/services/k8s_provider.py\">\nERROR [80:27] \"read_namespace\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [85:27] \"create_namespace\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [238:38] \"read_namespaced_deployment\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [246:40] \"replace_namespaced_deployment\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [256:36] \"create_namespaced_deployment\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [310:38] \"read_namespaced_service\" is not a known attribute of \"None\"\nERROR [318:40] \"repl